hori
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number: 2
Definition:
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1950s as a stage name for Maori dupe. [cf McCallum Half-Gallon Jar] ca1963 Wellington p.c. Brian Findlay, and William Maughan usual pron. [h ri:] `horrie' as in a contemporary song catchphrase `Morrie the Horrie.'
